'''''Rob-B-Hood''''' ({{zh-stp|s=宝贝计划|t=寶貝計劃|p=bǎobèi jìhuà|Cantonese:Bō Bui Wie Gack}}) is a 2006 [[action comedy]] film directed by [[Benny Chan]], starring [[Jackie Chan]], [[Louis Koo]] and [[Michael Hui]]. Set in [[Hong Kong]], ''Rob-B-Hood'' follows the lives of a gang of [[burglary|burglar]]s as they take care of a baby kidnapped from a wealthy family.

The film continues Jackie Chan's recent trend of including more [[drama|dramatic]] elements in his films, and is the first film in which he plays a bad person. The film's stunts, some of which involve the baby,<ref name="BC">{{cite web
  | title = Interview with Benny Chan
  | publisher = LoveAsianFilm
  | date = 2006
  | url = http://www.loveasianfilm.com/features/robbhood_feature02.html
  | accessdate = 2007-08-13 }}</ref> are personally performed by Jackie Chan and choreographed by the [[Jackie Chan Stunt Team]].<ref name = BJN>{{cite web
  | title = Jackie Chan slides down a water pipe in spite of his age (成龙春节大爬水管)
  | work = The Beijing News
  | date = [[2006-02-05]]
  | url = http://ent.thebeijingnews.com/0383/2006/0205/012@158883.htm
  | language = Simplified Chinese
  | accessdate = 2007-08-13 }}</ref> 

''Rob-B-Hood'' was released on [[September 29]], 2006 after ten months of production and received positive reviews from critics.<ref name = RT>{{cite web
| title = Rob-B-Hood at RottenTomatoes
| date = 2006-09-08
| url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/rob_b_hood/
| accessdate = 2007-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web
