The Japanese title of ''Rob-B-Hood'' is プロジェクトBB (''Purojekuto BB''), literally ''Project BB'', the name initially proposed for the film.<ref name = JP/> In Greece, the film is known as Ασύλληπτοι Απατεώνες (transliteration: ''Asulliptoi Apateones''), meaning ''Inconceivable Frauds''.<ref name = GR/>

The [[DVD region code|Region 3]] DVD was released in [[November]] [[2006]] and comes in two discs: A movie disc and an extras disc. The movie disc features both the cinematic and uncut versions of the film, along with a commentary track by Benny Chan. The extras disc contains a "behind-the-scenes" video, the [[post-production]] [[press conference]], a collection of deleted scenes and the music video of the [[theme music|theme song]].<ref>{{cite news 
  | title = Jackie Chan's Rob-B-Hood DVD now available
  | work = Screen Power
  | date = 2006-11-02
  | url = http://www.screen-power.com/competition.htm
  | accessdate = 2007-08-23 }}</ref> The DVD is currently unavailable to other regions.<ref name = "Twitch"/>

After the film's premiere at the Venice Film Festival, several scenes highlighting the personal relationships between characters were deleted from ''Rob-B-Hood'' prior to its release to the general public. Benny Chan explains including too many dramatic scenes may distract the audience from the plot.<ref name = "BC In"/> The uncut version of ''Rob-B-Hood'' can be watched by playing its DVD and selecting "Extended Version" at the main menu.<ref>{{cite video
  | people = Jackie Chan
  | title = Rob-B-Hood Festival Version
  | medium = DVD
  | publisher = JCE Productions
  | location = Hong Kong
  | date = 2007-09-08 }}</ref>

== Reception ==
[[Image:Project BB Japan.jpg|thumb|150px|Promotional poster of ''Project BB'' in Japan.]]
''Rob-B-Hood'' was well received by critics, despite having not received a rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] due the lack of reviews. Of the four reviews, three are positive, one neutral.<ref name = RT/> The film received praise at the Venice Film Festival for having a delicate balance between action and drama. Credit was given to the stunt choreography and the acting partnership of Jackie Chan and Louis Koo. The plot of ''Rob-B-Hood'' received mixed reviews: Some found it concise, hilarious and touching,<ref>{{cite web
| title = Rob-B-Hood creates both laughter and tears (《宝贝计划》一场欢笑一把泪)
| work = Xiao Xiang Chen Bao
| publisher = Sina
| date = 2006-09-28
| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/r/m/2006-09-28/07571266589.html
| language = Simplified Chinese
| accessdate = 2007-08-28}}</ref> whereas others criticised it for being unoriginal, similar to that of ''[[Three Men and a Baby]]''.<ref name = "Variety"/> In addition, reviewers questioned the inclusion of the female characters, whose actions are irrelevant to the plot.<ref>{{cite web
| last = Cheong
| first = Felix
| title = Jackie Chan now has a diaper-disaster movie to his name
| publisher = Channel NewsAsia
| date = 2006-09-29
| url = http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/moviesreviews/view/233120/1/.html
| accessdate = 2007-08-24 }}</ref>

''Rob-B-Hood'' grossed HK$1.2 million the day it was released in Hong Kong.<ref name=HK/> In China, the film topped the box office during the four day [[National Day of the People's Republic of China|National Day holiday weekend]], grossing [[Chinese Yuan|¥]]8.9 million.<ref>{{cite web
| title = Rob-B-Hood performs the best at the box office during the Golden Week (《宝贝计划》票房飘红 黄金周国产电影成牛市)
| work = 金羊网-新快报 
| publisher = Xinhua
| date = 2006-10-09
| url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/ent/2006-10/09/content_5180584.htm
| language = Simplified Chinese
| accessdate = 2007-08-26}}</ref> It went on to top the Chinese box office in October with box office figures exceeding ¥90 million.<ref name = Cbx/>''Rob-B-Hood'' performed well in [[Southeast Asia]], grossing US$404,000 in Singapore, US$400,000 in Malaysia and US$604,000 in [[Thailand]] during its first four days.<ref>{{cite web
| last = Rothrock
| first = Vicki
| title = "Rob-B-Hood" has $5 million opening session
| publisher = Variety
| date = 2006-10-04
| url = http://www.varietyasiaonline.com/content/view/110/
| accessdate = 2007-08-27 }}</ref> In total, ''Rob-B-Hood'' had a worldwide gross of US$20,434,179 despite not being released in North America and most of Europe.<ref name = numbers/>

